---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/Container.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Read our terms of service for Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates. Understand our policies, your responsibilities, and our commitment to your care."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-sage-50 to-warm-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mb-6">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Last updated: January 8, 2026
      </p>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-sage-50 p-6 rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] border border-sage-200 mb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed m-0">
            Welcome to Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates. By scheduling an appointment or using our services, you agree to these Terms of Service. Please read them carefully before your first visit.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Acceptance of Terms
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          By accessing our website, scheduling appointments, or receiving treatment at Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Services Provided
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates provides complementary and alternative healthcare services, including but not limited to:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-700">
          <li>Acupuncture treatments</li>
          <li>Traditional Chinese Medicine consultations</li>
          <li>Herbal medicine recommendations</li>
          <li>Cupping therapy</li>
          <li>Nutritional guidance and lifestyle counseling</li>
          <li>Other holistic health modalities</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Our services are designed to complement, not replace, conventional medical care. We encourage you to maintain regular communication with your primary care physician and other healthcare providers.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Patient Responsibilities
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Accurate Information
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          You agree to provide complete and accurate health information during your initial consultation and to update us about any changes to your medical condition, medications, or health status. Failure to disclose relevant health information may affect the safety and effectiveness of your treatment.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Following Treatment Plans
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          While we will provide personalized treatment recommendations, you are ultimately responsible for your own healthcare decisions. We encourage open communication about your treatment plan and any concerns you may have.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Communication
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          You agree to promptly notify us of any adverse reactions, changes in your condition, or concerns about your treatment. We maintain regular office hours and emergency contact protocols outlined in your patient materials.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Appointment Policies
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Scheduling and Confirmation
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Appointments can be scheduled by phone, email, or through our online booking system. You will receive a confirmation of your appointment via your preferred contact method. Please arrive 10-15 minutes early for your first appointment to complete necessary paperwork.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Cancellation Policy
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We understand that schedules change. If you need to cancel or reschedule your appointment, please provide at least 24 hours' notice. Cancellations made with less than 24 hours' notice may be subject to a cancellation fee of 50% of the session cost.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          No-Show Policy
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Failure to attend a scheduled appointment without prior notice will result in a charge equal to the full session fee. Repeated no-shows may result in a requirement to prepay for future appointments or termination of the patient-practitioner relationship.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Late Arrivals
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If you arrive more than 15 minutes late for your appointment, we may need to reschedule to ensure adequate treatment time and avoid disrupting other patients' appointments. You may be subject to our cancellation policy in such cases.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Payment Terms
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Payment Methods
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We accept cash, checks, and major credit cards (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover). Payment is due at the time of service unless other arrangements have been made in advance.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Insurance
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We are in-network providers for several insurance plans and can provide superbills for out-of-network reimbursement. Please verify your coverage before your appointment. You are responsible for any portions not covered by insurance, including deductibles, co-pays, and non-covered services.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Pricing
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Our current fee schedule is available upon request and may be updated periodically. We will notify you of any changes to pricing that may affect your care. Package deals and discounts may be available for multiple sessions paid in advance.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-charcoal mt-8 mb-4">
          Outstanding Balances
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Accounts with outstanding balances over 30 days may be subject to a monthly finance charge of 1.5% (18% APR). Accounts over 90 days past due may be sent to collections, and you will be responsible for all collection costs and legal fees.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Informed Consent and Treatment
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Before beginning treatment, you will be asked to sign an informed consent form acknowledging that you understand:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-700">
          <li>The nature of acupuncture and holistic treatments</li>
          <li>Potential benefits and risks</li>
          <li>Possible side effects and complications</li>
          <li>Alternative treatment options</li>
          <li>Your right to refuse or discontinue treatment at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          While serious side effects from acupuncture are rare, minor side effects may include temporary soreness, minor bleeding or bruising at needle sites, or temporary aggravation of symptoms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Scope of Practice and Limitations
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Our practitioners are licensed acupuncturists and traditional Chinese medicine practitioners. We do not diagnose or treat conditions outside our scope of practice. We do not:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-700">
          <li>Prescribe pharmaceutical medications</li>
          <li>Perform surgery or invasive procedures</li>
          <li>Provide emergency medical care</li>
          <li>Replace necessary conventional medical treatment</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          In cases requiring medical attention beyond our scope, we will refer you to appropriate healthcare providers.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Confidentiality and HIPAA Compliance
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We are committed to protecting your health information in accordance with HIPAA regulations. Your medical records and personal information will be kept confidential except as required or permitted by law. Please see our Privacy Policy for complete details on how we handle your information.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Minors and Consent
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Treatment of patients under 18 years of age requires consent from a parent or legal guardian. The parent or guardian must be present during the first visit and must sign all consent forms on behalf of the minor.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Intellectual Property
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          All content on our website, including text, graphics, logos, images, and educational materials, is the property of Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates and is protected by copyright laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or use any content without our written permission.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Website Use and Disclaimer
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Information provided on our website is for educational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice. The content should not be used for self-diagnosis or self-treatment. Always consult with a qualified healthcare provider for medical advice specific to your situation.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          While we strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, we make no warranties about the completeness, reliability, or accuracy of this information. Use of our website is at your own risk.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Limitation of Liability
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages resulting from your use of our services or website.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Our liability is limited to the amount paid for the specific service giving rise to the claim. This limitation applies whether the alleged liability is based on contract, tort, negligence, strict liability, or any other basis.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Professional Conduct
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We maintain professional boundaries and expect the same from our patients. Inappropriate behavior, harassment, or disrespectful conduct toward staff or other patients will not be tolerated and may result in termination of care.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Termination of Services
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Either party may terminate the patient-practitioner relationship at any time. If we terminate the relationship, we will provide you with reasonable notice and assistance in finding alternative care if requested. You may discontinue treatment at any time but remain responsible for payment of services already rendered.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Dispute Resolution
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          In the event of a dispute arising from these Terms of Service or your treatment, we encourage resolution through direct communication. If a dispute cannot be resolved informally, both parties agree to attempt mediation before pursuing legal action.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          These terms shall be governed by the laws of the State of Wisconsin. Any legal action must be brought in the courts of Milwaukee County, Wisconsin.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Changes to Terms
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be posted on our website with a revised "Last Updated" date. Continued use of our services after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the modified terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Severability
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If any provision of these Terms of Service is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision shall be limited or eliminated to the minimum extent necessary, and the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-charcoal mt-12 mb-6">
          Contact Information
        </h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-sage-50 p-6 rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] border border-sage-200">
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
            <strong>Acupuncture & Holistic Health Associates</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
            Bayshore Town Center<br>
            5800 N Bayshore Drive<br>
            Glendale, WI 53217
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
            Phone: <a href="tel:+14145551234" class="text-sage-600 hover:text-sage-700">(414) 555-1234</a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@holisticacupuncture.net" class="text-sage-600 hover:text-sage-700">info@holisticacupuncture.net</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-healing-blue/10 border border-healing-blue/30 p-6 rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] mt-8">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed m-0">
            <strong>Acknowledgment:</strong> By scheduling an appointment or receiving treatment, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to these Terms of Service.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
